## Icon Library
Always import icons from 'react-coolicons'. Never use @coolicons-dev/solid.

## Icon Name Mapping (Figma → Code)
| Figma Name | Component Name | Package          |
|------------|----------------|------------------|
| Info       | Info           | react-coolicons  |
| Show       | Show           | react-coolicons  |
| Add_Plus   | AddPlus        | react-coolicons  |
| Close_SM   | CloseSM        | react-coolicons  |


## Correct Usage
import { IconName } from '@coolicons-dev/solid';

// Size using token scale values
<IconName width={16} height={16} color={t.icon.default.subtle} />

## Rules
- Always pass color using icon tokens (t.icon.*.*)
- Never hard-code color values on icons
- Default icon size is 16x16 for inline, 20x20 for standalone
- leadingIcon?: React.ComponentType<{ width?: number; height?: number; color?: string }> 
  — optional icon component from react-coolicons to render at the start of the field
- trailingIcon?: React.ComponentType<{ width?: number; height?: number; color?: string }> 
  — optional icon component from react-coolicons to render at the end of the field

